<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[192,1440,545,794]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,324,674,698]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</emphasis>
We found a single specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[712,888,674,698]" class="Insecta" family="Kerriidae" genus="Austrotachardiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombiana">
<emphasis box="[712,888,674,698]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">A. colombiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the twig of a tree of the ‘Lorena’ cultivar. 
<taxonomicName box="[192,574,706,730]" class="Insecta" family="Kerriidae" genus="Austrotachardiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombiana">
<emphasis box="[192,574,706,730]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Austrotachardiella colombiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kondo, T. &amp; P. J. Gullan" box="[930,1243,705,730]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" pagination="395 - 401" refId="ref18327" refString="Kondo, T., and P. J. Gullan. 2005. A new species of Austrotachardiella Chamberlin on guava in Colombia (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Kerriidae), with a revised key to the species of the genus. Neotropical Entomology 34 (3): 395 - 401." type="journal article" year="2005">Kondo and Gullan (2005)</bibRefCitation>
based on specimens collected on two cultivars of guava, 
<taxonomicName box="[712,924,738,762]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Psidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="guajava">
<emphasis box="[712,924,738,762]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Psidium guajava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName box="[975,1110,738,762]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Myrtaceae</taxonomicName>
). This is the first record of this species on avocado worldwide. It is not considered a species of economic importance on avocados.
</paragraph>
